gEx(){return"In the first year of Jian'an, L\xfc Bu met his end at White Gate Tower. Cao Cao held the Emperor hostage to command the lords, Yuan Shao dominated the north, Sun Ce had just pacified Jiangdong, and Liu Bei took refuge in Xuzhou. Warlords vied for supremacy as the seeds of a three-way division began to sprout."},
gEy(){return"In the thirteenth year of Jian'an, Cao Cao led 800,000 troops southward while Liu Bei fled in defeat at Changban. The allied forces of Sun and Liu shattered Cao's army with fire at the Battle of Red Cliffs, establishing the foundation for the Three Kingdoms."},
gEz(){return"In the seventeenth year of Jian'an, Liu Bei was invited into Shu, secretly harboring ambitions to seize Yi Province. Cao Cao unified the north, Sun Quan held firm in Jiangdong, and the three-way struggle intensified."},
gEA(){return"In the third year of Jianxing, the late Emperor passed away and Liu Shan ascended the throne. Zhuge Liang, entrusted with the care of the young ruler, campaigned south against Meng Huo and north against Wei, devoting himself utterly to preserving the Han legacy."},
lB(a){return a+" AD"},
