A.aNK.prototype={
glc(a){return"Skip"},
Ew(a){return"Chapter "+a},
gxE(){return"196 AD. The Han Dynasty wavers, and ambitious lords rise across the land.\n\nCao Cao has escorted Emperor Xian to Xu, wielding imperial authority to command the feudal lords while recruiting the finest men of the age.\n\nYuan Shao, heir to four generations of Han ministers, dominates Hebei with a million soldiers, his gaze fixed on the Central Plains. Sun Ce secures six commanderies south of the Yangtze, founding what will become the mighty Wu.\n\nLiu Biao holds Jing Province in uneasy neutrality. Liu Bei wanders, a lord without land, seeking his moment.\n\nThe fate of the realm hangs in the balance. The era of decision has begun."},
gEt(){return"208 AD. Cao Cao leads his armies south in a campaign to end the age of division.\n\nLiu Biao's heir surrenders Jing Province without a fight. Liu Bei flees south, barely surviving the desperate stand at Changban.\n\nCao Cao's warships darken the Yangtze \u2014 800,000 men arrayed for the kill, poised to unite the realm under one banner.\n\nBut Sun Quan and Liu Bei forge an unlikely alliance. Zhou Yu harnesses the east wind, and a wall of fire at Red Cliffs shatters Cao Cao's dream of conquest.\n\nFrom the ashes of that inferno, three kingdoms emerge."},
gEu(){return"212 AD. Three powers divide the realm, and the balance grows ever more volatile.\n\nCao Cao commands the north in the name of the Han Emperor \u2014 whose authority now exists only in name.\n\nLiu Bei, guided by Zhuge Liang and Pang Tong, maneuvers into Shu under the guise of alliance, then reveals the iron fist within the velvet glove.\n\nSun Quan consolidates Eastern Wu, balancing external threats from Cao Cao with a flourishing internal order.\n\nThree kingdoms. Three visions for the realm. The contest enters its most critical phase."},
gEv(){return"225 AD. Liu Bei dies at White Emperor City, and an era passes.\n\nZhuge Liang, burdened with the charge of a dying emperor, takes sole responsibility for the survival of Han. He serves the young Liu Shan \u2014 but his true master is the dream of restoration.\n\nSeven times he captures Meng Huo; seven times he releases him. The south is pacified.\n\nNow the north calls. Cao Wei sits upon the heart of the old empire, and the Han heartland waits to be reclaimed.\n\nOut of the Qi Mountains, the Northern Expeditions begin \u2014 a brilliant mind against overwhelming odds, for the last hope of the Han."}}
